You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply on company site save-icon Job details Job Type Full-time Part-time Temporary Job Duties: Vice President with Goldman Sachs Bank USA in New York, New York. Manage Decision Platform for digital banking products responsible for onboarding customers for originating Card, Personal Loan and Deposit products. Develop and install code using C++, Java Script or Python. Implement Statistical/Machine Learning models on real time decision platforms. Partner with teams across various product verticals to manage and prioritize implementation of Credit and Fraud rules. Integrate the Platform for various product offerings and expand the scope of its usage by on boarding new data vendors and introducing software upgrades. Manage vendor relationship with 3rd party Platform provider and improve architecture design to integrate the platform across products and introduce new workflows. Assist team with hiring of new employees, training and development of junior team members. Supervise a team of highly talented developers across various geographic locations, to follow best practices for coding and platform maintenance and standardize the code development process. Develop reports and presentations on project progress and implementation pipeline for senior management and executive committees. Job Requirements: Bachelor’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Electrical, Electronics or Mechanical Engineering, Computer Science, Data Science, Business Intelligence or related field OR Master’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Electrical, Electronics or Mechanical Engineering, Computer Science, Data Science, Business Intelligence or related field. Five (5) years of relevant experience with Bachelor’s degree in the job offered or related role OR three (3) years of relevant experience with Master’s degree in the job offered or related role. Prior combined experience must include three (3) years with: working on technology-related projects, coordinating with stakeholders and driving a development strategy; working on several projects simultaneously and driving end-to-end project delivery. C++, Java Script or Python and object-oriented software engineering concepts; working with Statistical/Machine Learning models on real time decision platforms; using available technology, products and understanding pain points of data-based decision making; building data platforms including data extraction, clean-up and analysis; micro-service design and implementation, such as dedicated decision engines and/or orchestration layers; and negotiating competing priorities with various stakeholders to achieve project goals. Salary Range: The expected annual base salary for this New York, New York, United States-based position is $140,000 - $250,000. In addition, you may be eligible for a discretionary bonus if you are an active employee as of fiscal year-end. Benefits: Goldman Sachs is committed to providing our people with valuable and competitive benefits and wellness offerings, as it is a core part of providing a strong overall employee experience.
